                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client with leukemia who is receiving intravenous chemotherapy. The nurse reviews the laboratory results and notes that the white blood cell count is 2000 mm3 (2 × 109/L), the platelet count is 150,000 mm3 (150 × 109/L), the clotting time is 10 minutes, and the ammonia level is 20 mcg/dL (12 mcmol/L). Which nursing action would be appropriate?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe normal white blood cell count is 5000 to 10,000 mm3 (5 to 10 × 109/L). When the white blood cell count drops, neutropenic precautions need to be implemented. This includes protective isolation techniques to protect the client from infection. Bleeding precautions need to be initiated when the platelet count drops below 90,000 to 100,000 mm3 (90 to 100 × 109/L) or per primary health care provider prescription or agency policy. The normal platelet count is 150,000 to 400,000 mm3 (150 to 400 × 109/L). The normal clotting time is 8 to 15 minutes, and the normal ammonia level is 10 to 80 mcg/dL (6 to 47 mcmol/L). Removing the rectal thermometer from the client's room would be done if bleeding precautions were initiated. There is no useful reason to eliminate all protein from the diet.",
                        "id": "0e315831c8c24e138535b54258fb3044",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5ce337c999fb46dfb7abea947ad0d4c9",
                                "content": "Anemia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f2e2a34e76b84c7da9558a7a6ab640a8",
                                "content": "Decreased platelets"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
